tps://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cross, to traverse"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ford"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to swim (something)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to pass over"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to interpret","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"يَا أَيُّهَا ٱلْمَلَأُ أَفْتُونِي فِي رُؤْيَايَ إِنْ كُنْتُمْ لِلرُّؤْيَا تَعْبُرُونَ","english":"O people give me your opinion about my vision if you can see through it!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of عَبَرَ (ʕabara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"across"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to get across; to make cross, to cause to pass over, to convey across","tags":["ditransitive","literally","obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to get across; to express, to put into terms","tags":["ditransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to interpret","tags":["transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *ʕabar-. Compare Hebrew עָבַר (ʿāḇar, “to cross”), Old South Arabian 𐩲𐩨𐩧 (ʿbr, “to transgress”), Akkadian 𒁄 (ebēru, “to cross”).\n\nAdverbial accusative of عَبْر (ʕabr, “crossing”). Compare Old South Arabian 𐩲𐩨𐩧 (ʿbr, “towards”).\n\nCausative of the preceding verb عَبَرَ (ʕabara) and in the meanings of explaining, interpreting, expressing a semantic loan from Middle Persian [Book Pahlavi needed] (wtltn' /⁠widārdan⁠/, “to cause to pass”) = Early New Persian گذاردن (guḏārdan, “to cause to pass; to clean, to purge; to put, to place”), [Book Pahlavi needed] (wcʾltn' /⁠wizārdan⁠/, “to separate; to explain, to interpret, to express”) = گزاردن (guzārdan /gozârdan, “to cause to pass; to draw the outline of a picture; to express”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27826","headword_ar":"عَبْرٌ","root":"Ebr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiborN","text_ar":"عِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaboru A^asofaArK","text_ar":"عَبْرُ اَسْفَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaboru safarK","text_ar":"عَبْرُ سَفَرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see what here follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27828","headword_ar":"عِبْرٌ","root":"Ebr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K, TA, in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eiborap","text_ar":"عِبْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuborN","text_ar":"عُبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaborN","text_ar":"عَبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, A, K, TA, accord. to the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaborap","text_ar":"عَبْرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K,) of a river, (S, A, O,) and of a valley. (A, K.) En-Nábighah Edh-Dhubyánee says, of the Euphrates,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"taromiY A^awaA*iy~uhu AlEiborayoni biAlz~abadi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Its waves casting foam upon the two banks"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN fiY *`lika AlEibori","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ فِى ذٰلِكَ العِبْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is upon that side."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  See also the next preceding paragraph, in three places."}],"source_refs":["S","O","A","K"]},{"entry_id":"n27829","headword_ar":"عَبَرٌ","root":"Ebr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabira","text_ar":"عَبِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (AZ, T, &c.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuborN","text_ar":"عُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: ―         -b3-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaborapN","text_ar":"عَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27830","headword_ar":"عَبِرٌ","root":"Ebr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; and its fem., with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAbirN","text_ar":"عَابِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27831","headword_ar":"عُبُرٌ","root":"Ebr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuborN","text_ar":"عُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}